   "source": [
    "wind_reg = sm.ols(\"wind ~ wind_forecast\", data=df).fit(\n",
    "    cov_type=\"HAC\", cov_kwds={\"maxlags\": 48}\n",
    ")\n",
    "wind_reg.summary()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "dff9ccf6",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Corrected wind surprise: uncorrelated with the forecast.\n",
    "df[\"true_wind_error\"] = wind_reg.resid"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "4bc32984",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Linear model and diagnostics\n",
    "\n",
    "The first specification regresses the cash-out price on the NIV terms, the\n",
    "true wind error, net demand, and calendar dummies, with HAC standard\n",
    "errors for heteroskedasticity and serial correlation.\n",
    "\n",
    "The calendar dummies and the wind error are insignificant. The wind result is\n",
    "the first sign of mediation: once realised NIV is in the model, wind surprise\n",
    "has no separate effect on the price level, because its effect runs through the\n",
    "imbalance it creates. The model is then reduced to the NIV terms and net demand\n",
    "for the diagnostic stage."
   ]
  },
