   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "17ed2359",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The lag removes most of the autocorrelation in the residuals, but the squared\n",
    "residuals remain autocorrelated. This implies conditional\n",
    "heteroskedasticity, and it is the motivation for a GARCH variance model."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9c3978ec",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. GJR-GARCH\n",
    "\n",
    "The model is a GJR-GARCH with Student-t innovations and an AR(1) mean carrying\n",
    "the NIV and demand regressors. GJR is chosen over plain GARCH so the variance\n",
    "can respond asymmetrically to positive and negative shocks. The Student-t\n",
    "captures the heavy tails of cash-out prices. Regressors are scaled to\n",
    "gigawatts to help the optimiser converge."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 17,
   "id": "c1ab6f7f",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df[\"net_demand_gw\"] = df[\"net_demand\"] / 1000\n",
    "df[\"NIV_short_gw\"] = df[\"NIV_short\"] / 1000\n",
    "df[\"NIV_long_gw\"] = df[\"NIV_long\"] / 1000"
   ]
  },
